      "payload": {
        "kind": "agentTurn",
        "message": "[OBJECTIVE]\nExecute an hourly memory extraction job to synthesize facts and relational context from recent communications.\n\n[DATA ACQUISITION]\n1. Retrieve the exact current timestamp.\n2. Query sessions_history (limit=100) for the following session keys:\n - Nrexya main group\n - This updates group\n - Nemesis private DM\n3. Filter: Strictly discard any message older than exactly 60 minutes from the current timestamp.\n4. Process: Read every single remaining message in the 60-minute window. Zero skipping is permitted.\n\n[EXTRACTION PROTOCOL]\nAnalyze all retained messages. You must explicitly include banter and casual talk, as this contains high-density context. Extract and categorize:\n- Hard Data: Decisions, requests, bugs, changes, and agreements.\n- Context & Vibe: Mood, tone, frustrations, satisfaction, unspoken implications, implicit preferences, successful humor, and friction points.\n\n[OUTPUT & STORAGE]\n1. Append the summary directly to the end of today's daily memory file.\n2. You must format the appended text exactly according to this Markdown template. Do not deviate, and do not add conversational introductory text:\n\n---\n## 🕒 [HH:MM AM/PM] Snapshot\n\nFacts\n* [Bullet points of hard facts, decisions, bugs, etc.]\n\nContext & Tone\n* [Bullet points of mood, unspoken context, jokes, etc.]\n---\n\n3. Validation constraint: If messages exist within the window, you MUST extract and write the data. Only write the timestamp header and \"No messages\" if the 60-minute dataset is absolutely empty.\n\n[EXECUTION & ERROR HANDLING]\n- Success: Run 100% silently. Do NOT trigger notifications, send confirmation messages, or output conversational filler anywhere. Output only to the memory file.\n- Failure Override: If the job fails, encounters an execution error, or cannot read/write to the required files, you must immediately send a failure notification detailing the error to the updates group."
